Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, glycosuria, and ketonuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal). Blood glucose and HbA1c are low-normal. These findings suggest impaired renal function, likely nephrotic-range proteinuria, and possible tubular dysfunction. No evidence of urinary tract infection. Further nephrological evaluation is recommended.
